Unilever, who makes the following labels: Dove, Degree and Axe, has come out with a great technology: Dry Spray Antiperspirant! This is a must have for someone ... perfect for those with sensitivity issues, as it is tough on sweat and soft on skin. I tried out two formulas, Dove Dry Spray and Degree MOTIONSENSE Dry Spray Fresh Energy. My husband tried out three of them, Dove Men+Care Dry Spray Clean Comfort, Degree MOTIONSENSE Adventure and Axe White Label Night. Antiperspirant 3.8 oz./107 g $6.99This deodorant/antiperspirant has notes of apple, citrus mixed with a floral powder cream. I love ... great for me but I wanted my daughter to try it too. She found this one worked better than the Dove Dry Spray as she perspires more than I do. She loved this one! It does seem to help as you perspire more. There are other scents: Shower Clean, Sheer Powder, Sexy Intrigue and Peach Burst. Dove Men+Care Dry Spray Clean Comfort 3.8 oz./107 g $6.89.This features a clinically proven and non-irritating formula that is tough on ... skin. White Stallion Ranch in Tucson, Arizona Dude ranches in the American Southwest conjure up all sorts of romanticized imagery, from horses grazing near cacti in the morning to a lone cowboy strumming his guitar by a fire after sunset. The American Southwest has captured our collective imagination and resulting movies (like City Slickers) have led to the popularization of dude ranch vacations for a taste of that purely American “Wild West” experience. That experience, and so much more, is there for the taking at the White Stallion Ranch in Tucson, Arizona.
Saguaro Cactus on White Stallion Ranch property in Tucson
A multigenerational family vacation and the 3,000 acre property White Stallion Ranch are perfectly suited for each other. We took our kids and my parents-in-law to the ranch for a family vacation, and everyone had a flawlessly great time. We were there for four days, and we rode horses (at least) once every day. There’s more to White Stallion Ranch than horse riding, of course, but that quickly became our favorite ranch activity. We chose slow rides and fast rides; other options are mountain rides, all-day and half-day rides, team cattle penning — this is one we really want to try the next time we’re on a dude ranch, by the way — wine and cheese rides and the even classier beer and cheetoes rides, lessons, and hay rides.
Multigenerational Horseback Riding at White Stallion Ranch
Family hike on huge White Stallion Ranch property in Tucson, Arizona
But, for my urban and suburban family, a long weekend of extended horseback riding through the brush was a continual highlight. Sure, it’s a lifestyle for plenty of folks, but this really make our vacation just what we wanted it to be. The horses are happy and healthy, gentle and sweet (one of mine was very stubborn, too, about nibbling on some reedy grasses while walking through them). The guides are obviously also happy to be there and show city folk the slower life on a working ranch. Four days, six different half-day rides, and every one left us looking to sign up for more. We didn’t “get” the appeal of long, exploring horseback rides before, but now we do.
Happy horses (and kids) at White Stallion Ranch in Arizona
There are lots of other activities at the White Stallion Ranch too, here is a quick list:
•    Horseback riding
•    Hiking
•    Hayrides
•    Rock Climbing
•    Swimming
•    Tennis
•    Volleyball
•    Rec Room Gaming
•    Petting Zoo
•    Cookouts
•    Live Evening Entertainment
That’s a lot of activities! Certainly enough to keep a multigenerational family vacation on the ranch occupied. We only rode horses and hiked, and..well, ate a lot if eating counts as a vacation activity! The meals here are ranch style, delicious and plentiful. It’s pretty amazing, how riding horses for a few hours whets the appetite. Something of note is that the wine menu here is classy; even my oenophile father-in-law was impressed. Drinking a couple glasses of wine as the sun sets in the desert, and a farm hand starts strumming his guitar and singing nearby, is a memory my parents-in-law, husband and I will take with us forever.
Stables at White Stallion Ranch in Arizona
The White Stallion Ranch in Tucson, Arizona borders the Saguaro National Park, and those amazing saguaro cacti are everywhere. Since these are very slow-growing plants, those giant saguaro cacti  are easily a hundred years old. These cacti are protected and only found in this part of Arizona. It’s an hour and a half flight from Los Angeles to Tucson, but the topography is so distinct, it feels like being in a different country. Honestly, it’s an ideal desert vacation for beleaguered suburbanites; I get the whole “City Slickers” thing now. Even a few days at the White Stallion Ranch is enough to feel relaxed, rejuvenated and ready to face the rest of the world.

One activity off the ranch that the staff are happy to arrange is a hike to petroglyphs at Signal Hill in the Saguaro National Park. The hike is very easy, though it’s usually pretty hot (this IS part of the Sonoran Desert, after all). While it’s not what I’d call an accessible hike, it is only about half a mile with limited elevation changes, with a path that is usually easy to see and use. Signal Hill has lots of petroglyphs from the Hohokam, a pre-Columbian people who marked stones with some desert animals, and even more geometric designs whose true meanings are lost to time.
Petroglyphs on Signal Hill, Saguaro National Park
I participated in the National Park-guided hike to Signal Hill’s petroglyphs the last morning of our multigenerational vacation at White Stallion Ranch in Tucson. The rest of my family opted for — you guessed it — one last half day horseback ride. It was amazing to see the vast expanse of the desert, quite literally as far as the eye could see, and imagine the Hohokam eking out their lives there from around 400 AD to the mid-1400’s. Dove Dry Spray Review 

I tried Dove’s cool essentials dry Spray and I really like it.  Dove Dry Spray antiperspirant goes on instantly dry.  I didn’t experienced any wetness at all when I sprayed it on unlike ... flaking on my skin.  The spray went on sheer and remained sheer the entire time I had it on.

 



Dove Dry Spray I received was the cool essentials fragrance.  The smell was amazing.  It could have easily been a body spray it smells so good.  I tested the Dove antiperspirant while I was visiting my mother.  I sprayed it on my arm to get her opinion of the smell. ... the smell was very pleasant and she’d try it herself even though she doesn’t prefer spray deodorants.



I received the Dove Men + Care Clean Comfort Dry Spray also.  I had my brother try it.  He told me it when on ... pleasant.  He said he’d be comfortable wearing the it with or without his regular cologne because the scent wasn’t overpowering.








Dove Dry Cool Essential Spray is one of 6 new fragrances making a total of 8 sprays available for women.  The Dove Men + Care Clean dry spray line has 4 options.
 




You can find out more about Dove and their new dry sprays at Facebook.com/DoveUs or Twitter using the social handle @Dove and hashtag #TryDry.  For the Dove Men + Care Clean Comfort Dry Spray use the social handle @DoveMenCare or on Facebook at Facebook.com/dovemencareus





Dove Dry Spray is available at Walmart and Target.

The Janet Yellen Era Starts Here After seven long years, the era of zero-level, short-term U.S. interest rates is at an end, at least for now. In raising the federal funds rate by a quarter of a percentage point on Wednesday, Janet Yellen and her colleagues at the Federal Reserve signaled that, in their view, the U.S. economy, which has been hooked up to a monetary life-support machine since December, 2008, is now strong enough to withstand slightly higher borrowing costs. At a press conference following the announcement of the rate hike, a reporter asked Yellen, who took over the Fed at the start of 2014, how average Americans should interpret the central bank’s action. She said people should know that the Fed’s decision “reflects our confidence in the economy.” While economic conditions vary across regions and across industries, “we see an economy that is on a path of sustainable improvement,” Yellen went on. “I hope they take it as a signal that conditions will continue to strengthen, and jobs prospects will be good.” Another reporter brought up the possibility that raising interest rates might hurt the economy or even tip it into recession. In the mid-nineteen-thirties the Fed, believing that the Great Depression was over, started to tighten monetary conditions, only to see the economy fall into another slump, which forced the bank to reverse course. Roughly the same thing happened to the central bank of Japan in 2000 and 2001, and to Sweden’s central bank a few years ago. Some prominent analysts, including the hedge-fund manager Ray Dalio (whom I profiled in 2011), have warned that the Fed could be in danger of repeating its error. In recent months, Lawrence Summers, whom Yellen beat out for the Fed post, has also argued that, with inflation quiescent and much of the world facing economic weakness, this is no time for the Fed to be tightening monetary policy and raising rates. Earlier this week, on his blog, Summers conceded that the Fed, having repeatedly signalled its intention to raise the federal-funds rate, needed to go ahead with the hike to preserve its credibility in the markets. But he also reminded his readers that inflation is still well below the Fed’s target of two per cent, and he urged Yellen and her colleagues to go easy in the months ahead. Yellen was at pains to point out that the Fed won’t rush into further hikes, and that it would monitor closely what was happening to the inflation rate. But she also dismissed concerns about the economy slipping back into recession. “I feel confident about the fundamentals driving the economy,” she said. She pointed to a healthy employment picture—2.3 million new jobs created this year—and strong growth in household demand, particularly for new cars and trucks. There is always the possibility that a negative shock will hit the economy, Yellen conceded. But she said that she didn’t see anything to be overly concerned about at the moment. Yellen also argued that raising interest rates gently now could help to prolong the economic recovery, which began in the summer of 2009 and is already the fifth-longest on record. In the past, she pointed out, the Fed had sometimes waited too long to tighten policy, and, eventually, an overheating economy had forced it to raise rates more dramatically, bringing about a recession. “It is because we don’t want to cause a recession . . . that it is prudent to begin early and gradually,” Yellen said. If we were living in more normal times, this would be a winning argument. As Yellen also pointed out, it now takes a considerable amount of time for the effects of interest-rate hikes to feed through the economy. If policy-makers want to influence what happens in 2016 and 2017, now is the time for them to get started. According to internal projections that the Fed published on Tuesday, the members of its policy-making committee expect the federal funds rate to rise to 1.4 per cent by the fourth quarter of 2016. Assuming the Fed moves in quarter-point increments, this suggests that there will be four more rate hikes between now and then. The weakness in Yellen’s argument is that, from some perspectives, the economic world still seems far from normal. In the past six months, the price of oil has fallen from more than sixty dollars to below thirty-six dollars, bringing down the price of gas and that of many other energy products. Meanwhile, the value of the dollar has continued to rise, bringing down the price of imported goods. Largely as a result of these factors, inflation has virtually disappeared. In November, the consumer price index didn’t rise at all. Over the past twelve months, it has risen by just 0.5 per cent. During the press conference, Yellen repeatedly argued that the disappearance of inflation is a temporary phenomenon, which will reverse in the coming months and years. Dove launches Dove Baby at 60th anniversary celebrations Daddy T loves buying bulk and one of the things he regularly stocks up on is Dove shower gels and deodorants. Since he’s a loyal customer to the brand I was pretty thrilled to text him from the Dove 60th anniversary celebrations on Wednesday and let him know that he could now even start buying Dove for the children.
Dove has this week launched Dove Baby, a range including nappy cream, baby wipes, head to toe wash, shampoo and lotion, which was presented at the brand’s 60th anniversary celebrations. There are two Dove Baby ranges–one called rich moisture and one called sensitive moisture. Both product ranges are hypoallergenic, but the sensitive range is ... tried samples of the products at home, and the best part about this new range is the pump on the Dove Baby Head to Toe Wash. The pump makes it super easy to use when bathing baby and children and I’m ... 20-month-old Baby Boy and four-year-old Big Girl. I like sticking to sensitive products for Big Girl too, and the new Dove Baby Sensitive wash is a nice good value fragrance-free option.

Dove Baby was launched in Tesco this week, and the range will be available from Boots and Asda from mid-March

お騒がせセレブ、ベラ・ソーンが若手女優への“ガールクラッシュ”を明かし、ファン熱狂! ここ最近、露出のすごいファッションやぶっちゃけ発言でお騒がせクィーンとなっているベラ・ソーン。そんな彼女が新たな恋?とも取れる発言をしたことに対し、”最高のカップル”とファンは大盛り上がり!
PHOTO:Shutterstock/AFLO, Backgrid/AFLO
左:ダヴ・キャメロン、右:ベラ・ソーン
スコット・ディシックと交際数日で破局し、グレッグ・サルキンと元サヤに戻ると思いきや、またもスコットとの噂が浮上......と、このところ恋愛関係が派手なベラ・ソーン。そんな彼女が先日ツイッターにて「やっばーい。ワイフにしたいわ」と若手女優のダヴ・キャメロンの写真をアップしてコメント。かつては「次は女の子と恋をしたい」と語り、バイセクシャルを公表したベラだけに、つぶやきを見たファンたちは「このふたりの恋愛を応援する」と大騒ぎ!
一方、指名されたダヴにも今年1月に共演女優キーアージー・クレモンズとのキス動画をアップしたり、「女性が大好き」とツイッターで明かしたりといった過去が。しかもベラの「ワイフにしたい」というコメントに、「ひざまづいてくれたら、可能性はあるわ」とつぶやき返したから、またもファンは大熱狂!
実は過去にも、互いへの好意をツイッターで明かしたことのあるふたり。ダヴは現在俳優のトーマス・ドハティと交際中だから、現実になる可能性は低いけど、ポジティブ全開でキュートなふたりだからこそ、ファンが“お似合い”と応援したくなる気持ちは十分分かる!
TEXT:MARIKO PEELING

After reading the ... minute. We tend to judge too quickly on social media platforms.

If you are confused... let me fill you in.
Dove UK created a few campaign images that have a strong controversial message.

Now if you know the brand DOVE well enough, you would know that they love adding unique messages to their marketing – especially when launching new products. Remember the Real Beauty campaign?
Baby Dove recently launched worldwide and the campaign message for this launch was “Trust your way”. Dove believes that there is no RIGHT way, there is only YOUR way. And you should trust your way because you ... MY way of parenting. I wasn’t going to let someone else tell me how to mother my child.
The Baby Dove advert says “75% say breastfeeding in public is fine, 25% say put them away. What’s your way?”
Now to me, ... brand but I have worked with them however that has nothing to do with my opinion here.

パンク&Tシャツ文化の伝説を目撃!@DIESEL アートをキャンバスから解き放ち、ストリートファッションの起源を作ったのが英国出身のジョン・ドーヴと、テキスタイルデザイナーモーリー・ホワイトのアートユニット「ジョン・ドーヴ & モーリー・ホワイト」。1968年に「WONDER WORKSHOP」名義でフルグラフィックのプリントTシャツを制作したことが、新しい流行の幕開けだった。この時スタジオを構えていたパディントンにある廃工場には、詩人やペインター、デザイナーなどのアーティストが集い、実験的な試みが行われていた。時期を同じくしてニューヨークでは、イギー・ポップ率いるザ・ストゥージズたちが活躍したことで、イギリスとアメリカのカルチャーにおける相互作用が始まりパンクの時代が動き出す。
「Tシャツは資本主義の現代世界の産物であり、そこから生まれた社会主義革命の一つなのです。 それは普遍的な言語の一部であり、ポップアートのポスターよりもパーソナルで、音楽よりも痛烈な表現だったのです」と語る2人は、のちにヴィヴィアン・ウエストウッドやマルコム・マクラーレン、そしてシド・ヴィシャスとも交流していく。
日本で初開催となる本展は、彼らが歩んできた時代と、同時期に過ごした人物や出来事を振り返る内容。今では当たり前になったアイデアの起源をスクリーンプリントとコラージュ、そして映像で体感できる。キュレーションを担当するのはクラインシュタイン(KLEINSTEIN CO.,LTD)の小石祐介。かつて彼らが所属するロンドンのPAUL STOLPER GALLERYと共に「Iggy Pop Jacket」、また「Strawberry Jacket」のプロジェクトを手がけた人物だ。現在でも自らプリントを製作し続けるジョン・ドーヴ & モーリー・ホワイト。過去50年の活動に息づく反抗心とユーモアをお見逃しなく。
